Re posting from last thread

For all my fellow writefags who feel they are unworthy, fucking stop that shit right now. I've been in that mindset. It's a bad habit to get into, always looking down on yourself and your work like that. It leads to a lack of improvement. Sure, you're not the best, but that doesn't mean it's pointless to keep trying. Every step is a learning experience.
As I said, I've been down that road of such serious self-doubt self-depreciation and masking it all with "jokes" and attempting to downplay my achievements and works. It wasn't healthy, and it took a long time for me to work through those issues.
Do not stare into the abyss and then blink. Force IT to blink. Make IT the small one, the weaker aspect. Beat down those negative moments, remember the fact you're still here, still writing, still gathering an audience. Little by little, you are improving.
TL;DR: Stop beating yourself down. It only compounds your problems and makes the hole you're in deeper. It's time to climb out. If you need a helping hand to do so, reach out. We're here for you.
I love my fellow /hmofa/ggots. No homo. You guys are great.
